{"author":{"id":"5b985e369ac0336ec1d64454401e459885cb0dcd026e1f9cb5035b70bc1a84dc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1667479828,"nonce":"Gj58kZVgMY4HjJpvALLKrgc3kwk=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5VgmL0","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4896","origin":"github"},"title":"Tool request: virFinder","message":"The package provides functions to predict viral sequences in a fasta file, such as the assembled contigs from metagenomic data. The method has good prediction accuracy for short (~1kb) and novel viral sequences.\n\nThe prediction method is based on the sequence signatures (k-tuple word frequencies) that distinguish viruses from host sequences. The model was trained using an equal number of known viral and host sequences. For a query sequence, the number of occurrences of k-tuple words is first counted by a c++ program using a hash table. Then the sequence is predicted based on the k-tuple word frequencies using a logistic regression model trained with previously known sequences.\n\nTool repository: https://github.com/jessieren/VirFinder","files":null}]}